<li id="cite_note-362"><b><a href="#cite_ref-362" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFVan_Hove1994">Van Hove, Brian (1994). <a href="http://www.ewtn.com/library/HOMELIBR/FR94204.TXT" class="external text" title="http://www.ewtn.com/library/HOMELIBR/FR94204.TXT" rel="nofollow">Blood-Drenched Altars "Blood Drenched Altars"</a>. EWTN Global Catholic Network<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.ewtn.com/library/HOMELIBR/FR94204.TXT" class="external free" title="http://www.ewtn.com/library/HOMELIBR/FR94204.TXT" rel="nofollow">http://www.ewtn.com/library/HOMELIBR/FR94204.TXT</a> Blood-Drenched Altars</span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 9 March 2008</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Blood+Drenched+Altars&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Van+Hove&amp;rft.aufirst=Brian&amp;rft.au=Van+Hove%2C+Brian&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.pub=EWTN+Global+Catholic+Network&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ewtn.com%2Flibrary%2FHOMELIBR%2FFR94204.TXT+Blood-Drenched+Altars&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Roman_Catholic_Church"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-363"><b><a href="#cite_ref-363" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.state.gov/documents/organization/9001.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.state.gov/documents/organization/9001.pdf" rel="nofollow">"International Religious Freedom Report 2001"</a> (PDF). US Department of State. 2001<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.state.gov/documents/organization/9001.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.state.gov/documents/organization/9001.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.state.gov/documents/organization/9001.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 13 March 2008</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=International+Religious+Freedom+Report+2001&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.pub=US+Department+of+State&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fdocuments%2Forganization%2F9001.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Roman_Catholic_Church"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Norman167-364"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Norman167_364-0" title="">^</a></b> Norman, p. 167–168.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Chadwick266-365"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Chadwick266_365-0" title="">^</a></b> Chadwick, Owen, p. 266.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Chadwick240-366"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Chadwick240_366-0" title="">^</a></b> Chadwick, Owen p. 240.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Norman172-367"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Norman172_367-0" title="">^</a></b> Norman, p. 167–172.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Vidmar329-368"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Vidmar329_368-0" title="">^</a></b> Vidmar, p. 329.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Vidmar327-369">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Vidmar327_369-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Vidmar327_369-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Vidmar, p. 327–33l</li>
<li id="cite_note-Pham45-370"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Pham45_370-0" title="">^</a></b> Pham, p. 45, quote: "When Pius XI was complimented on the publication, in 1937, of his encyclical denouncing Nazism, <i>Mit Brennender Sorge</i>, his response was to point to his Secretary of State and say bluntly, 'The credit is his.'"</li>
